        "type": "api_key",
        "label": "Honeycomb API key",
        "generateUrl": "https://docs.honeycomb.io/api/key-management/create-an-api-key",
        "setup": "Create it in Honeycomb under **Account → Team Settings → API Keys** or via the [Key Management API docs](https://docs.honeycomb.io/api/key-management/create-an-api-key). Honeycomb issues three key families: Ingest, Configuration, and Management. For API access, use the key type required by the endpoint; Ingest and Configuration keys are passed in `X-Honeycomb-Team`, while Management keys are used as `Authorization: Bearer <key-id>:<secret>`. The secret/token is only shown at creation time, so save it immediately."
      },
      "hc_mcp_oauth": {
        "type": "oauth2",
        "label": "Honeycomb MCP OAuth",
        "generateUrl": "https://docs.honeycomb.io/integrations/mcp/configuration-guide",
        "setup": "Connect your MCP host to Honeycomb using the OAuth flow described in the [MCP configuration guide](https://docs.honeycomb.io/integrations/mcp/configuration-guide). Honeycomb recommends OAuth for interactive agents; many hosts can finish the login from their built-in MCP setup or via a command such as `claude mcp add` / `qchat mcp add` shown in the docs. After authorization, the host stores the resulting access token for MCP use."
      }
    },
